<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<title>astro-font-devtools playground</title>
		<style>
			:root {
				--font-heading: system-ui, sans-serif;
				--font-title: system-ui, sans-serif;
				--font-body: system-ui, sans-serif;
			}
			body {
				font-family: var(--font-body);
				max-width: 42rem;
				margin: 4rem auto;
				padding: 0 1.5rem;
				line-height: 1.6;
			}
			h1 {
				font-family: var(--font-title);
			}
			h2 {
				font-family: var(--font-heading);
			}
			code {
				font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>Astro Font Devtools Playground</h1>
		<p>
			Open the dev toolbar at the bottom of the screen, pick <strong>Font Devtools</strong>, and
			swap fonts <em>live</em>. Three targets are pre-seeded:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li><code>--font-heading</code></li>
			<li><code>h1</code></li>
			<li><code>p</code></li>
			<li><code>code</code></li>
			<li><code>.additional-notes</code></li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			You can also arbitrarily specify fonts for <code>--font-title</code> and <code
				>--font-body</code
			>.
		</p>
		<h2>Additional Notes</h2>
		<p class="additional-notes">
			For regular selectors you can also apply weight and italic styles. Custom properties only
			accept a font family.
		</p>
	</body>
</html>
